scab
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a highly-infectious disease of sheep, caused by a mite Dematodecles ovis [rife among NZ flocks between 1845 and 1892.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: note from previous hdwd: the sheep disease of early NZ (1845-46) has been general English since 14 cent. (OED) see discards @n and @v get quote: Scab Act 1848
